The presence of a possible space charge limited current (SCLC) transport mechanism in the device has also been explored. The high value of n, presence of large series resistance and a low zero-bias barrier height indicate that thermionic emission is not the only current transport mechanism operational at higher voltages (region II). In this region, the behaviour of the forward bias current is typical of a SCLC transport mechanism, controlled by trap levels. The relation for the current I in this case is given by following equation [37]: 7I∞98ϵϵ0aμV2d3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
